# Kaikoura Hospital Site Act 1911Local Act1911 No 14

Date of assent21 October 1911

## Contents

[Title][0]
    
*   [Preamble][1]

[1][2] [Short Title][2]

[2][3] [Authority to issue certificate of title for a site for a hospital][3]

---

An Act to provide for the Transfer of certain Land to the North Canterbury Hospital and Charitable Aid Board as a Site for a Hospital.
    
*   #### Preamble
    
    WHEREAS by Proclamation dated the twentieth day of August, nineteen hundred, certain land in the Marlborough Land District, being Section No 410, Town of Kaikoura, containing nineteen acres two roods twenty-four perches, was taken under the authority of section [thirty-two][4] of The [Reserves, Endowments, and Crown and Native Lands Exchange, Sale, Disposal, and Enabling Act 1898][5], and The Public Works Act 1894, for the purposes of a recreation-ground and site for a cottage hospital: And whereas by Order in Council dated the tenth day of August, nineteen hundred and nine, control of the said land (being part of the Kaikoura Domain) was vested in the Kaikoura Domain Board: And whereas it is desired to transfer part of the said land to the North Canterbury Hospital and Charitable Aid Board as a site for a hospital:

BE IT THEREFORE ENACTED by the General Assembly of New Zealand in Parliament assembled, and by the authority of the same, as follows:---

##### 1 Short Title
    
*   This Act may be cited as the Kaikoura Hospital Site Act, 1911\.

##### 2 Authority to issue certificate of title for a site for a hospital
    
*   (1.) The Governor is hereby authorized and empowered to execute a Warrant for the issue of a certificate of title under The Land Transfer Act 1908, in favour of the North Canterbury Hospital and Charitable Aid Board, in respect of such part of Section No 410, Town of Kaikoura, not exceeding two acres, as is agreed upon by the said Board and the Kaikoura Domain Board.
    
    (2.) Upon the issue of a certificate of title as aforesaid, the land to which the certificate relates shall be held by the North Canterbury Hospital and Charitable Aid Board in trust as a site for a hospital for the reception and relief of persons requiring medical or surgical treatment, and of persons suffering from disease.



